        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 7:40PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 739 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Mantua, or 12 miles east of Aliceville, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Snoddy, Englewood, Ralph, Northport, Little Sandy, Maxwell,
Moundville Airport, Union, Fosters Boat Landing, Hull, Mound State
Park, Stillman College, McFarland Mall, Pleasant Ridge, Lewiston,
Benevola, Elliots Creek, Shelton State Community College, Tuscaloosa
Amphitheater, and Bryant Denny Stadium.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
west central Alabama.</instruction>
